==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Continental pronunciation
<hw>Continental pronunciation</hw> <pr>(of Latin and Greek.)</pr> <def>A
method of pronouncing Latin and Greek in which the vowels have their
more familiar Continental values, as in German and Italian, the
consonants being pronounced mostly as in English. The stricter form of
this method of pronouncing Latin approaches the Roman, the modified form
the English, pronunciation. The Continental method of Greek
pronunciation is often called <stype>Erasmian</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Continental system</ent>⟦br⟧
